<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-1770] cassandra-cli help output should mention the need for semicolons</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1770</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running cassandra-cli for the first time after upgrading beta3 -&amp;gt; rc1, I thought it was broken, because any command I typed (&quot;?&quot;, &quot;quit&quot;, &quot;exit&quot;, &quot;use system&quot;, etc) just printed some empty space and sat there until I killed it. I didn&apos;t know it was a continuation prompt, or that semicolons were needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The startup banner message currently says:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Connected to: &quot;Test Cluster&quot; on localhost/9160
Welcome to cassandra CLI.

Type &apos;help&apos; or &apos;?&apos; for help. Type &apos;quit&apos; or &apos;exit&apos; to quit.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe that the example commands should have semicolons after them, to let the user know about the change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, a &quot;?&quot; by itself should probably not require a semicolon.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Debian squeeze with 0.7.0~rc1 package installed&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
